This file contains the CGI End Use Potential vocabulary, as defined by the IUGS Commission for Geoscience Information (CGI) Geoscience Terminology Working Group. The vocabulary defines concepts to specify the end-use potential of the Earth Resource (eg for energy, fertilizer, building raw material etc). In the ERML model, a MineralOccurrence is a kind of EarthResource that has an occurrence type category and one or more associated enduse potential concepts. This vocabulary provides the range of values for the end-use potential property of MineralOccurrence. By extension, this vocabulary includes all concepts in this conceptScheme, as well as concepts in any previous versions of the scheme.
